observations.recommendation:
We recommended the Municipal Mayor to enjoin coordination among the department heads concerned to comply with the requirements of COA Circular No. 2015-008, specifically to require the:
Municipal Engineer to:
Provide the Municipal Accountant and the Property Custodian/ Supply Officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for every road project, as well as the report on the repair/ maintenance of each local road network; and
Reconcile with the Municipal Accounting Office the reports on the Local Road Network.
Property Custodian/ Inventory Committee to:
Conduct an inventory of the local roads under the Municipality’s jurisdiction with the assistance of the Municipal Engineering Office; and to prepare the Report on the Physical Count of the Road Network (RPCLRN);
Maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map; and
Maintain a complete Local Road Network Property Card (LRNPC) for all roads and its components and reconcile the same with the records of the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Engineer;
Municipal Accountant to:
Maintain the LRNLC for each Local Road Components with complete description;
Reconcile the LRNLC with the Local Road Inventory and Road Map of the Supply Office and Report on Local Road Network of the Municipal Engineering Office;
Provide the correct depreciation for each road component and make the necessary adjustment to correct the understatement of Accumulated Depreciation recognized for the Road Network account; and
Ensure complete disclosure of the total Road Network System in the Notes to the Financial Statements.

We recommend to the Local Chief Executive to require the:

Inventory Committee, in coordination with the Supply Officer, to annually conduct the complete the physical count of all properties, through the preparation of the RPCPPE, reconcile the result of the inventory with the balances recorded by the Municipal Accountant to ensure the existence, completeness and accuracy recorded in the PPE accounts in the financial statement;

Supply Officer to maintain the PC which should be reconciled with the PPELC maintained by the Accounting Office

Require the inventory team to identify the causes of the deficiencies; determine if PPEs were lost, accountable persons involved, and determine liability or accountability on lost PPEs;

Direct the Municipal Accountant to drop from the books disposed items using the original copy of the Waste Material Report (WMR) and Inventory and Inspection Report for Unserviceable Property (IIRUP), when properly authorized in accordance with applicable regulations, as basis for adjusting the accounts affected by means of a journal entry voucher.

We recommended to the Local Chief Executive to require the:

Inventory Committee, in coordination with the Supply Officer, to annually conduct the complete physical count of all properties, prepare the RPCPPE, and reconcile the result of the inventory with the balances recorded by the Municipal Accountant to ensure the existence, completeness and accuracy reported PPE accounts in the financial statement;

Municipal Accountant to maintain the PPELC which should be reconciled with the PC maintained by the Supply Officer; 

Supply Officer to maintain the PC which should be reconciled with the PPELC maintained by the Accounting Office.

Require the inventory team to identify the causes of the deficiencies; determine if PPEs were lost, accountable persons involved, and determine liability or accountability on lost PPEs;

Direct the Municipal Accountant to drop from the books disposed items using the original copy of the Waste Material Report (WMR) and Inventory and Inspection Report for Unserviceable Property (IIRUP), when properly authorized in accordance with applicable regulations, as basis for adjusting the accounts affected by means of a journal entry voucher.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct:

the MDRRMO to review and update annually the LDRRMFIP and include the PPAs to be charged to PY Unexpended LDRRMF;

The Municipal Accountant and Budget Officer to regularly reconcile their records to determine the remaining available balance; 

The Accountant to:

Transfer any unexpended current year LDRRMF to the Trust Fund at the end of the year and maintain subsidiary ledger by year of transfer of the unexpended LDRRMF; 

Include in the LDRRMF Fund Utilization Report the available and utilized PY balances;

Disclose in the Notes to Financial Statements the amount and details of the unexpended balance of LDRRMF using the prescribed format;

Check and insure the completeness of the supporting documents of DVs; and,

Stop recording purchase of inventories charged to the LDRRM Fund as outright expense instead correctly record in the appropriate inventory account.

We recommended for the Municipal Mayor to:
1. Require the Inventory Team to conduct the reconciliation process of the PPE and RPCPPE;
2. Require the inventory team to identify the causes of the deficiencies; determine if PPEs were lost, accountable persons involved, and determine liability or accountability on lost PPEs;
3. Direct the Municipal Accountant to drop from the books disposed items using the original copy of the Waste Material Report (WMR) and Inventory and Inspection Report for Unserviceable Property (IIRUP), when properly authorized in accordance with applicable regulations, as basis for adjusting the accounts affected by means of a journal entry voucher.
4. Require the GSO - Designate to secure the donation papers of the 5 units of motor vehicles received from the donors and submit the documents to the Municipal Accountant for the recognition in the books.
5. Require the Municipal Accountant to: (a) record in the books the cost of the 5 items of motor vehicle received from donors; and (b) make the necessary adjustment to correct the erroneous recording of non-PPE items costing P322,476.00.

