The Municipal Accountant
a. to reconcile the General Ledger and Subsidiary Ledgers of the Due
to NGAs account in General Fund;
b. to update and submit to the Auditors the Subsidiary Ledgers of the
accounts in Trust Funds;
c. to initiate the preparation of final Fund Utilization Reports and
refund unutilized balances to the SAs;
d. to revert the PDAF balance amounting P6,309.77 to the
unappropriated surplus of the general fund.

We have recommended that Management:

cancel the lease contracts of lessees who do not operate or manage their own leased stalls/spaces and lease the same to other interested applicants subject to the approval of the Municipal Mayor;



Regularly monitor the occupancy status of the lessees of commercial spaces to ensure compliance with their respective lease contracts thru the Office of the Market Supervisor and the Municipal Treasury.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
Require the InventoryTeam to conduct the reconciliation process of the PPE and RPCPPE;
Require the inventory team to identify the causes of the difficiencies; determine if PPEs were lost, accountable persons involved, and determine liability or accountability on lost PPEs;
Direct the Municipal Accountant to drop from the books disposed items using the original copy of the Waste Material Report (WMR) and Inventory and Inspection Report for Unserviceable Property (IIRUP), when properly authorized in accordance with applicable regulations, as basis for adjusting the accounts affected by means of a journal entry voucher.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct:
the MDRRM Officer to fully  and timely implement the PPAs to ensure the immediate implementation and completion of ongoing and unimplemented projects in order to effectively increase the level of preparedness of the community from the occurrence of natural calamities and mitigate the risk of damaged in case of disaster;
the MDRRMO to prepare and submit a monthly report thereon in accordance with the suggested format;
direct the LDRRM Council to regularly monitor and evaluate its implementation.
the Municipal Accountant to use the disclosure format for MDRRMF in the Notes to financial statement as required by regulations.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the Municipal Accountant to:
(a) secure the latest bank statement for all accounts;
(b) prepare the bank reconciliation statements;
(c) record all valid reconciling items, if any, in accordance with the provisions stipulated in Section 74 of PD 1445: and
(d) review balances in the books and related records and correct discrepancy of P 3,000,000.00.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the Municipal Accountant and General Services Officer (GSO)-Report of Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) Designate to:
1. Direct the Municipal Accountant and GSO-Designate to exert effort to reconcile the PPE account of the municipality;
2. Direct the GSO-Designate to provide with unit values of PPE items listed in the Report of Physical Count of PPE (RPCPPE).
3. Compel the Accountant and GSO-Designate to abide with the capitalization threshold of P15,000.00 as required;
4. Direct the Municipal Accountant and Mun. GSO-Designate to maintain PPELC and PC respectively.
